\
The next morning, Dorian assembled his men and instructed them to visit the next two towns down each road, then report back. That would fit within Reece\'92s orders and give some indication which way Ephraim went. He told them to ask for a preacher or smith, working on the theory Ephraim was using his trade. They broke up and headed to the stable to ride on.\
A few minutes later, Sergeant Tailor returned with a sheepish look on his face. \'93Sir, Doris has a limp.\'94\
\'93Sergeant, I don\'92t know what you do with your mounts. They always come up limp.\'94\
\'93I dunno, sir. It\'92s not like I had them growing up.\'94 Sergeant Tailor\'92s accent came from the worst parts of London.\
Ensign Mabbott knew where they found him, a jail not much farther from there. \'93Fine. Take myBlack Betty. She\'92s rock steady. But go easy on her. She\'92s still a bit wild.\'94}